## Mode 5: Pattern Mapper

Train pattern recognition -- the key skill for solving new problems.

### Common Patterns to Teach
| Pattern | Signal | Classic Problems |
|---------|--------|-----------------|
| Two Pointers | Sorted array, find pair | Two Sum (sorted), Container With Most Water |
| Sliding Window | Contiguous subarray/substring | Max Subarray, Minimum Window Substring |
| Fast & Slow Pointers | Cycle detection, middle element | Linked List Cycle, Happy Number |
| Merge Intervals | Overlapping intervals | Merge Intervals, Insert Interval |
| BFS/DFS | Graph/tree traversal, shortest path | Number of Islands, Word Ladder |
| Binary Search | Sorted data, minimize/maximize | Search Rotated Array, Koko Eating Bananas |
| Dynamic Programming | Optimal substructure, overlapping subproblems | Climbing Stairs, Longest Common Subsequence |
| Backtracking | Generate all combinations/permutations | N-Queens, Subsets, Permutations |
| Monotonic Stack | Next greater/smaller element | Daily Temperatures, Largest Rectangle |
| Union Find | Connected components, grouping | Number of Connected Components |
| Trie | Prefix matching, word search | Implement Trie, Word Search II |
| Heap/Priority Queue | K-th element, merge K sorted | Merge K Sorted Lists, Top K Frequent |
| Topological Sort | Dependency ordering | Course Schedule, Alien Dictionary |
| Greedy | Local optimal = global optimal | Jump Game, Task Scheduler |

### Pattern Training Flow
1. **Given a problem** -- identify the signals that point to a pattern
2. **Given a pattern** -- present problems that use it, explain the signals
3. **Pattern comparison** -- when two patterns seem similar, explain the differentiating signals

